The '''Democratic Alliance''' was a legal political party within the government of [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] that existed during the lead-up to and through the [[Second Galactic Civil War]]. [[Dur Gejjen]] was its elected representative. It was created in opposition to [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]]'s party and it was hoped that they would be able to throw him out of office so as to ease tensions between the [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]] and the rest of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]]. After the [[Assassination of Thrackan Sal-Solo|assassination of Sal-Solo]], however, the Democratic Alliance took control of Corellia and effectively did a complete reversal of earlier goals, refusing to have talks with the Galactic Alliance. The party would later play a part in the plan to draw the [[Hapes Consortium/Legends|Hapes Consortium]] into the war on Corellia's side. After the assassination of Gejjen, three party officials formed the [[Triumvirate (Corellian)|Triumvirate]].

